parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or death to the occupants.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated
the passenger seat airbag light blinks
the airbag warning light remains on after the ignition is turned off
the airbag warning light comes on intermittently
the airbag warning light stays on after the seatbelt is buckled
the airbag warning light does not come on when the seatbelt is unbuckled.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the SRS warning light can indicate a problem with the airbag system, which can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or death to the occupants.
symptoms: The SRS warning light is illuminated
the SRS warning light stays on after the ignition is turned off
the SRS warning light comes on intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to repair the airbag system according to the recall can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or death to the occupants.
symptoms: The part needed to repair the airbag system is unavailable
the repair takes an unreasonable amount of time
the repair is not done correctly
the vehicle is deemed unsafe to drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Failure of motor mounts can cause the engine to shift position, leading to serious consequences, including engine damage, loss of control, and accidents.
Failure of the radiator and cooling system can cause engine overheating, damage, and failure, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Failure of the catalytic converter can cause noxious odors, nausea, and respiratory problems, as well as engine performance issues.
symptoms: Noxious sulfur odor inside and outside the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Air intake leak and surging can cause loss of control, accidents, and engine damage.
